thread.title: More than 60 injured, houses damaged in Indonesian quake

author: news24.com
title: More than 60 injured, houses damaged in Indonesian quake
text:
Sorong - More than 60 people were injured and 200 houses damaged on Friday when a powerful earthquake rocked remote eastern Indonesia, a disaster agency official said, and warned the number of victims could rise.
People were woken up and ran screaming out of their homes when the 6.6-magnitude undersea quake struck in the Papua region at about 01:00, not far from the coastal city of Sorong.
Seventeen people were so far known to have sustained serious injuries and 45 to have suffered minor injuries, while 200 houses were damaged, said disaster agency spokesperson Sutopo Purwo Nugroho.
No deaths have so far been reported. The quake also caused blackouts in Sorong and patients were evacuated from a hospital in the city.
